Gamesa Corp. Tecnologica SA, Spainâ€™s
biggest maker of  wind turbines , will provide 44 megawatts of
power equipment to Globeleq Mesoamerica Energy for a project in
southwestern Nicaragua, the company said today in an e-mailed
statement.  Gamesa will install 22 of its G90 turbines in the town of
Rivas and later connect the wind farm to the grid, Zamudio,
Spain-based Gamesa said. Globeleq Mesoamerica Energy is owned by
